article.headline: North Texas 106, Cameron 53
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Collin Dennis scored 21 points off the bench, and four other North Texas players finished in double figures to lead the Mean Green in a 106-53 win over Cameron on Saturday night. Tristan Thompson added 16 points and Josh White had 14 for North Texas (1-0), which scored more points in the second half (54) than Cameron did the entire game. Leslie Malone scored 19 points and Terrance Welch had 12 for Cameron (0-1). Adam McCoy added 13 points and Ben Bell had 10 for North Texas.
